An October 2020 study by the V-Dem Institute found that the Republican party had become increasingly illiberal in recent decades, appearing to follow a similar trajectory to authoritarian parties such as Fidesz of Hungary, the AKP of Turkey and the BJP of India. The study found “data shows that the Republican party in 2018 was far more illiberal than almost all other governing parties in democracies.” [259][260][261][262]
